Step 1. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• Formula: Turnover = Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
• Accounts Receivable at beginning = 0.00 and at end = 1,502,354.84  
• Average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 1,502,354.84) / 2 = 751,177.42  
• Main Business Revenue = 5,565,589.48  
• Therefore, Ratio = 5,565,589.48 / 751,177.42 ≈ 7.41  

Step 2. Operating Cash Flow Ratio and Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
(For this task the two ratios are computed the same way.)  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -81,548.37  
• Total Current Liabilities at end = 728,279.50  
• Ratio = -81,548.37 / 728,279.50 ≈ -0.11  

Step 3. Total Asset Turnover Ratio  
• Formula: Turnover = Revenue / Average Total Assets  
• Total Assets at beginning = 13,000,000.00 and at end = 14,823,650.85  
• Average Total Assets = (13,000,000.00 + 14,823,650.85) / 2 = 13,911,825.43  
• Therefore, Ratio = 5,565,589.48 / 13,911,825.43 ≈ 0.40  

Step 4. Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Formula: Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity  
• In the balance sheet, the only liabilities provided are the current liabilities = 728,279.50  
• Total Owner’s Equity at end = 14,095,371.35  
• Therefore, Ratio = 728,279.50 / 14,095,371.35 ≈ 0.05  

Thus, the solution in JSON format is:
  
{
  "solution": {
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "7.41",
    "operating cash flow ratio": "-0.11",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-0.11",
    "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.40",
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.05"
  }
}
